<h1>Problem 1713 - 2023 Bundeswettbewerb Mathematik, Round 2, P4 of 4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Between the vertices of a regular polygon with \(2n\) sides, \(n\) connecting lines (edges and diagonals) are coloured red. The following properties hold:
<ol><li> Each vertex of the polygon is the endpoint of exactly one red coloured segment.</li><li> No two red coloured segments have the same length.</li></ol>
Determine all positive integers \(n\geq2\) such that this is possible.</p>
